<item>
            <title>[AMQ-4904] jdbc ioexception handler can restart transports in error after lease expriy</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-4904</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When the db is unavailable the jdbcioexception handler will suspend by stopping the transport connectors and will await a successful checkpoint on the jdbc store before a restart.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If the db becomes available btween the check for lock and the checkpoint, it is possible to try and restart the transports without the lock, in error.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We need to validate the lock after we stop our wait for the checkpoint.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
